  "slug": "gvrs-villager-variants",
  "title": "GvR's Villager Variants",
  "description": "Makes villagers & illagers able to have different eye colors, so you can finally tell them apart!",
  "body": "**This resource pack reqiures either Entity Texture Features, Optifine, or whatever other alternative there is.**\n\nDid you ever wish you could tell your villagers apart from one another without the use of name tags? Did you ever wish that villagers were more like their own individuals? Do you just want everything to have 500 different variants for some reason? Well buddy, then this is the resource pack for you!\n\nThis resource pack adds 6 eye color variants, **without** touching skin tones, because we all know what will happen if we add different skin stones. 😐\n\nFor it to be _extra_ vanilla, the eye colors were taken from Minecraft Dungeons.\n\nThe variants are:\n- Amber\n- Magenta (yes, eyes can be magenta)\n- Blue\n- Gray\n- Brown\n- Dark Bluish-Green\n\nAnd, don't you worry! We (just me, there's only one person working on this) kept in the original green!\n\nBut wait, I have also added variants for the illagers and witches!\n\nThe Illager variants are:\n- Evoker Green\n- Vindicator Blue\n- MCD Illager Blue (very slightly darker version of Vindicator Blue)\n- Jade\n- Ultra Dark Brown\n- Ultra Dark Gray\n\nThe Witch variants are:\n- Witch Purple\n- MCD Witch Purple (slightly lighter version of Witch Purple)\n\nIf there are going to be more in Minecraft Dungeons II, they will be added.",
